outcome.review_summary: Solid, well-structured implementation of a file-backed inference cache with clean config integration, proper opt-in behavior, and a thorough PR description. The cache module itself is production-ready with good error handling (corrupt entry recovery, clean invalidation). Tests are well-organized covering key generation, hit/miss, invalidation, and opt-in behavior, but lack integration-level tests against the actual ModelEvaluator (tests only simulate evaluator logic with inline if-statements rather than exercising the real _infer_record path), and miss edge cases like concurrent access or non-JSON-serializable outputs. Missing mandatory configuration.md update for the new cache config section.
